<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!-- App Sandbox is disabled in Release.
	     Reason: the app spawns a bundled Chromium child for CDP scraping +
	     identify flows. Under App Sandbox the spawned Chromium inherits the
	     parent's narrow sandbox profile, hits SIGABRT in its main thread
	     during early init (codeSigningMonitor:2, abort() in Chromium Framework,
	     no usable Chrome console output), and never binds its CDP port —
	     observed deterministically in v0.14.x even with Hardened Runtime
	     entitlements (allow-jit + disable-library-validation + allow-unsigned-
	     executable-memory) set on BOTH the outer .app and the nested
	     Chromium.app. The known cure is to not sandbox the outer app; this
	     forfeits Mac App Store eligibility, which is already deferred per
	     docs/app-store.md. Hardened Runtime remains on for notarization. -->
	<key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
	<false/>
	<!--
	v0.21.31 — AMFI / -413 SIGKILL fix.

	REMOVED from the HOST entitlements (were present in v0.21.30 and earlier):
	  - com.apple.security.application-groups
	  - keychain-access-groups

	Why removed:
	  Both are AMFI-restricted entitlements on macOS Sonoma+. Restricted
	  entitlements require an embedded Developer ID provisioning profile
	  (`Contents/embedded.provisionprofile`) to validate at exec time. The
	  Sparkle distribution flow uses `method=developer-id` and ships
	  PROFILE-FREE, so v0.21.30 signed the host with these entitlements but
	  had NO embedded profile — every fresh launch triggered:
	    amfid: Restricted entitlements not validated, bailing out.
	      Error: Code=-413 "No matching profile found"
	    taskgated-helper: Disallowing com.ethansk.macos-widgets-stats-from-website
	      because no eligible provisioning profiles found
	  and the kernel SIGKILL'd the host process before main().

	Why removing both is safe:
	  1. App-group data sharing — the host is UNSANDBOXED in Release
	     (`app-sandbox = false` immediately above). It has direct
	     filesystem access to `~/Library/Group Containers/<id>/`
	     without the entitlement. AppGroupPaths.sharedContainerURL()
	     was updated in v0.21.31 to FALL BACK to building that path
	     manually when `containerURL(forSecurityApplicationGroupIdentifier:)`
	     returns nil. The widget extension keeps its entitlement (it's
	     sandboxed and MUST go through the security API), so both
	     processes still meet at the same physical directory and shared
	     data still flows.
	  2. Keychain sharing — KeychainHelper.swift already candidates
	     `[sharedAccessGroup, nil]` and falls back to the default access
	     group (implicitly the team-id-prefixed bundle-id) when the
	     entitlement is missing. The MCP shared-secret token is only
	     read/written by the host process; the widget never touches it.

	DO NOT re-add either entitlement here without ALSO embedding a
	Developer ID Direct Distribution provisioning profile in the bundle.
	The build-time `require_profile_app_group_entitlement` check in
	scripts/build.sh was authored against an older expectation that one
	would exist; in the Sparkle/Developer-ID path it doesn't, hence the
	AMFI break. If the provisioning-profile path is ever revived, update
	BOTH this file AND scripts/build.sh + scripts/sign-release.sh to
	embed the profile + re-introduce the validator.
	-->
	<key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
	<true/>
	<!-- Hardened Runtime exceptions required to spawn the bundled Chromium child.
	     Chromium's V8 needs JIT-able pages (allow-jit + allow-unsigned-executable-memory),
	     and its frameworks are signed by Google's team identity so dyld must skip
	     library validation when our sandboxed parent process loads them.
	     Without these three, the spawned Chromium quits immediately and CDP never binds.
	     See scripts/embed-chromium.sh for the corresponding nested-bundle entitlements. -->
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
